<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-78-0914 </DOCNO><TEXT>The book informs about the causes and effects of air pollution and acidrain. Teachers and students are given access to measuring methods analyzingthe major constituents of rain water. Although analyses are based buton simple and transparent chemical reactions requiring but single andreasonably priced instruments, the quantitative results obtained areprecise. Besides, access is given to the evaluation of the analyticalresults obtained and to today's feasible air pollution abatement methods.</TEXT></DOC>